---
import SeoPage from "../../../components/SeoPage.astro";

const sections = [
  { h2: "Apollo vs Clay in plain English", paragraphs: [
    "Apollo is primarily a database + sequencing workflow for outbound teams. Clay is a data automation layer that can enrich, score, and generate highly tailored inputs at scale.",
    "If your goal is volume fast, Apollo can get you moving. If your goal is relevance at scale across multiple data sources, Clay usually wins."
  ]},
  { h2: "When Apollo is enough", paragraphs: [
    "You have a tight ICP, simple enrichment needs, and your main constraint is sending volume and basic personalization.",
    "You need fast list building, simple sequences, and reporting without building a complex workflow."
  ]},
  { h2: "When Clay wins", paragraphs: [
    "You need multi-source enrichment, AI research summaries, scoring, routing, and rule-based segmentation.",
    "You want to build a repeatable workflow that improves over time, not just blast bigger lists."
  ]},
];
---
<SeoPage
  title="Apollo vs Clay"
  description="A practical comparison of Apollo and Clay for outbound teams: when to use each and how they fit together."
  sections={sections}
/>
